1
00:00:05,260 --> 00:00:06,240
(The first full meeting)

2
00:00:06,250 --> 00:00:07,170
We're back.

3
00:00:07,550 --> 00:00:08,880
The new guest is here.

4
00:00:08,880 --> 00:00:09,566
What do you think

5
00:00:09,577 --> 00:00:10,840
about the new guy?

6
00:00:10,840 --> 00:00:11,600
Not telling you.

7
00:00:11,800 --> 00:00:13,110
Feels like it's almost over.

8
00:00:13,310 --> 00:00:14,720
They could all be your type.

9
00:00:14,880 --> 00:00:16,470
I value how we get along.

10
00:00:16,470 --> 00:00:18,390
If it's one-sided, you'd let it go.

11
00:00:18,550 --> 00:00:19,360
It'll be exhausted.

12
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:20,840
I've never felt

13
00:00:20,840 --> 00:00:22,230
such tension before.

14
00:00:23,860 --> 00:00:28,660
=Live and Love S2=
=We're on Balance Island=

15
00:00:28,820 --> 00:00:32,580
(Day 2 of the secret date)

16
00:00:32,590 --> 00:00:33,790
Did you sleep well last night?

17
00:00:33,790 --> 00:00:34,520
Not bad.

18
00:00:34,520 --> 00:00:35,790
I passed out instantly.

19
00:00:36,270 --> 00:00:37,336
You had to wake up early.

20
00:00:37,347 --> 00:00:38,880
Maybe we can go back earlier at night.

21
00:00:38,880 --> 00:00:39,560
Yeah.

22
00:00:39,880 --> 00:00:40,880
Let me see your hand.

23
00:00:42,630 --> 00:00:43,430
Not bad.

24
00:00:44,016 --> 00:00:44,840
What about this side?

25
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:46,430
Much better now.

26
00:00:46,950 --> 00:00:47,880
Yeah, it's better.

27
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:48,880
Let's eat.

28
00:00:48,880 --> 00:00:50,560
Go ahead. Let's go.

29
00:00:50,560 --> 00:00:51,940
(Happy)

30
00:00:52,113 --> 00:00:53,560
(A hearty breakfast)
Foodies again.

31
00:00:53,560 --> 00:00:54,170
How nice.

32
00:00:54,181 --> 00:00:54,790
So nutritious.

33
00:00:54,790 --> 00:00:56,240
Look at all this fruit.

34
00:00:56,630 --> 00:00:57,720
So nutritious.

35
00:01:00,460 --> 00:01:01,980
(Eats enthusiastically)

36
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:03,000
What kind of bun is this?

37
00:01:03,011 --> 00:01:03,560
This one is...

38
00:01:03,560 --> 00:01:04,160
Savory.

39
00:01:04,160 --> 00:01:04,870
Is it BBQ pork?

40
00:01:04,870 --> 00:01:05,830
BBQ pork bun.

41
00:01:07,190 --> 00:01:07,830
So lucky.

42
00:01:07,830 --> 00:01:09,480
Is the food on the island so good?

43
00:01:09,780 --> 00:01:11,380
(Silent)

44
00:01:11,440 --> 00:01:12,230
Just okay?

45
00:01:13,040 --> 00:01:13,550
Well.

46
00:01:13,550 --> 00:01:15,950
I haven't been on the island much.

47
00:01:15,950 --> 00:01:16,820
(Barely stayed)

48
00:01:17,960 --> 00:01:18,986
I asked the wrong person.

49
00:01:19,590 --> 00:01:19,910
Yeah.

50
00:01:19,910 --> 00:01:21,000
I'll ask someone else later.

51
00:01:21,400 --> 00:01:22,440
I got "banished".

52
00:01:23,760 --> 00:01:26,000
Looking forward to anything?

53
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:28,190
First thing you wanna do?

54
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:31,360
No idea.

55
00:01:31,360 --> 00:01:32,800
I think once we get there,

56
00:01:32,800 --> 00:01:33,720
they'll have

57
00:01:33,720 --> 00:01:35,040
another task for us.

58
00:01:35,360 --> 00:01:36,760
There might be a game at once.

59
00:01:36,760 --> 00:01:37,040
Yeah.

60
00:01:37,720 --> 00:01:38,270
A game.

61
00:01:38,270 --> 00:01:39,510
I wanna play a game.

62
00:01:39,510 --> 00:01:41,510
But I'm a little nervous.

63
00:01:43,160 --> 00:01:43,800
It might be...

64
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:44,550
Intense?

65
00:01:44,550 --> 00:01:45,160
Yeah, intense.

66
00:01:45,171 --> 00:01:45,830
I don't think so.

67
00:01:45,830 --> 00:01:47,000
When girls play games,

68
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:48,910
it's usually pretty chill.

69
00:01:49,230 --> 00:01:50,360
Love and peace.

70
00:01:50,830 --> 00:01:51,270
Exactly.

71
00:01:51,720 --> 00:01:52,950
It's just you guys.

72
00:01:52,950 --> 00:01:54,550
Yeah, tense for guys.

73
00:01:57,870 --> 00:01:59,360
What's your favorite food?

74
00:02:00,080 --> 00:02:01,230
I love hot pot.

75
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:02,000
Hot pot?

76
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:03,040
What kind of hot pot?

77
00:02:03,760 --> 00:02:05,160
Sichuan hot pot.

78
00:02:05,360 --> 00:02:06,360
Spicy?

79
00:02:06,360 --> 00:02:07,680
What about numbing?

80
00:02:08,123 --> 00:02:09,520
I can eat it, just not my favorite.

81
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:11,390
It's a normal extent.

82
00:02:19,080 --> 00:02:19,880
Thanks.

83
00:02:21,886 --> 00:02:22,910
This sunshine feels great.

84
00:02:22,910 --> 00:02:23,720
Yeah.

85
00:02:23,720 --> 00:02:24,440
It's so bright.

86
00:02:25,416 --> 00:02:26,030
Let's sit here.

87
00:02:26,830 --> 00:02:27,670
Thanks.

88
00:02:30,180 --> 00:02:31,300
(Facing the sun)

89
00:02:32,366 --> 00:02:33,110
Too bright for you?

90
00:02:33,110 --> 00:02:33,960
It's dazzling, right?

91
00:02:34,270 --> 00:02:35,960
I can barely open my eyes.

92
00:02:36,390 --> 00:02:38,000
You should wear shades later.

93
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:38,830
Yeah.

94
00:02:39,563 --> 00:02:40,160
It's dazzling.

95
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:40,830
Seriously.

96
00:02:42,440 --> 00:02:42,910
Well.

97
00:02:42,910 --> 00:02:43,390
Last night,

98
00:02:43,880 --> 00:02:44,630
did you sleep well?

99
00:02:45,080 --> 00:02:46,240
Honestly, not really.

100
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:47,080
How about you?

101
00:02:47,080 --> 00:02:48,360
Pretty well.

102
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:49,526
I fell asleep once I got back.

103
00:02:51,113 --> 00:02:52,440
You said you've been here before.

104
00:02:53,110 --> 00:02:54,390
Did you ever eat here?

105
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:55,160
Nope.

106
00:02:55,160 --> 00:02:55,910
Not even once?

107
00:02:55,910 --> 00:02:56,440
No.

108
00:02:58,240 --> 00:02:59,600
But it's gorgeous here.

109
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:00,270
Did you notice?

110
00:03:00,466 --> 00:03:00,792
Yeah.

111
00:03:00,803 --> 00:03:01,600
That sea over there.

112
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:03,110
As I told you, it's stunning.

113
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:04,880
That round spot.

114
00:03:04,880 --> 00:03:07,110
It's a check-in spot at the hotel.

115
00:03:07,470 --> 00:03:08,670
Have you checked in there?

116
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,110
No.

117
00:03:10,110 --> 00:03:12,270
I sat on one of the lounge chairs

118
00:03:12,270 --> 00:03:13,630
and took some photos.

119
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:16,390
Here they come.

120
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:18,670
I'm seriously starving.

121
00:03:18,830 --> 00:03:19,630
Me too.

122
00:03:19,630 --> 00:03:20,270
Thanks.

123
00:03:20,370 --> 00:03:20,980
Thanks.

124
00:03:22,880 --> 00:03:24,960
Do you eat a lot in the morning?

125
00:03:25,240 --> 00:03:26,960
Yeah, I eat a lot

126
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:27,520
for breakfast.

127
00:03:28,550 --> 00:03:29,320
Since you work out,

128
00:03:29,320 --> 00:03:31,000
I guess you like eggs.

129
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,000
I love eggs.

130
00:03:32,390 --> 00:03:33,160
Ten a day.

131
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:34,190
(That many!)
What?

132
00:03:34,190 --> 00:03:35,000
Ten a day.

133
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:36,240
Ten eggs a day?

134
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:37,000
Seriously?

135
00:03:37,160 --> 00:03:37,550
Yep.

136
00:03:38,080 --> 00:03:39,830
Boiled or fried?

137
00:03:39,830 --> 00:03:41,000
Or sunny-side up?

138
00:03:41,270 --> 00:03:42,360
Mostly sunny-side up.

139
00:03:43,320 --> 00:03:45,240
I don't eat that many in one meal.

140
00:03:45,240 --> 00:03:45,830
Well.

141
00:03:45,830 --> 00:03:46,750
Yeah.

142
00:03:46,750 --> 00:03:48,160
Three meals in total.

143
00:03:48,550 --> 00:03:50,750
Have you tried salted duck eggs?

144
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:52,470
Yeah, the kind you have with congee,

145
00:03:52,470 --> 00:03:52,960
right?

146
00:03:53,550 --> 00:03:54,080
Exactly.

147
00:03:55,270 --> 00:03:56,160
Do you like it?

148
00:03:56,346 --> 00:03:57,160
I actually like it.

149
00:03:57,160 --> 00:03:58,320
I'm from Yangzhou.

150
00:03:58,520 --> 00:04:00,910
If we have congee in the morning,

151
00:04:00,910 --> 00:04:03,270
we pair it with salted duck eggs.

152
00:04:04,266 --> 00:04:05,240
What about century egg?

153
00:04:05,550 --> 00:04:06,110
Century egg?

154
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:07,720
I like it too.

155
00:04:07,946 --> 00:04:08,498
Me too.

156
00:04:08,509 --> 00:04:09,945
During the Chinese New Year holiday,

157
00:04:09,956 --> 00:04:11,440
we usually serve cold dishes,

158
00:04:11,440 --> 00:04:12,440
including century eggs.

159
00:04:12,770 --> 00:04:13,630
Century egg with tofu.

160
00:04:13,750 --> 00:04:15,083
We serve the century egg straight.

161
00:04:15,720 --> 00:04:18,200
With a slightly dry texture.

162
00:04:19,550 --> 00:04:20,720
Have you been to Yangzhou?

163
00:04:20,720 --> 00:04:21,640
I don't think so.

164
00:04:21,640 --> 00:04:22,040
Nope.

165
00:04:22,550 --> 00:04:23,760
I should go sometime.

166
00:04:24,230 --> 00:04:26,600
Any special snacks?

167
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:28,106
Have you heard of Yangzhou fried rice?

168
00:04:29,440 --> 00:04:30,350
Yeah.

169
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:32,320
What else?

170
00:04:32,320 --> 00:04:33,390
Any other specialties?

171
00:04:33,390 --> 00:04:34,270
Local snacks.

172
00:04:34,790 --> 00:04:35,920
Crab roe soup dumplings.

173
00:04:36,440 --> 00:04:37,110
That kind.

174
00:04:38,440 --> 00:04:39,720
(Gestures)
So big.

175
00:04:40,440 --> 00:04:42,040
Is that for one person or...?

176
00:04:42,110 --> 00:04:43,110
Yep, single serving.

177
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:45,390
It's kind of flat in shape.

178
00:04:46,640 --> 00:04:48,040
You mean like a pancake?

179
00:04:48,760 --> 00:04:50,320
It's not upright.

180
00:04:52,226 --> 00:04:53,553
Aren't you scared of butterflies?

181
00:04:54,510 --> 00:04:55,510
It's really pretty.

182
00:04:55,510 --> 00:04:56,163
That butterfly.

183
00:04:57,670 --> 00:04:58,510
When you eat that,

184
00:04:58,510 --> 00:04:59,720
they'll give you a straw.

185
00:05:00,160 --> 00:05:01,600
You poke a little hole

186
00:05:01,830 --> 00:05:03,000
and then sip out

187
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:04,550
the crab roe soup inside.

188
00:05:04,550 --> 00:05:06,480
Drink it before you eat it.

189
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:07,270
Right.

190
00:05:07,670 --> 00:05:09,350
You like quite a lot of foods.

191
00:05:09,950 --> 00:05:10,390
Yeah.

192
00:05:11,110 --> 00:05:12,230
You're such a foodie.

193
00:05:13,040 --> 00:05:14,320
You think I'm like a foodie?

194
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:16,600
Sounds like it.

195
00:05:21,320 --> 00:05:22,440
So much bread.

196
00:05:22,440 --> 00:05:23,600
Do you like carbs?

197
00:05:25,510 --> 00:05:26,640
I love carbs so much.

198
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:27,830
(Loves carbs)
You love carbs?

199
00:05:27,830 --> 00:05:28,600
Carb hero.

200
00:05:28,830 --> 00:05:29,670
Rice is my favorite.

201
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:30,510
Rice.

202
00:05:35,640 --> 00:05:37,830
We're meeting them in a bit.

203
00:05:37,830 --> 00:05:38,940
(Feeling uneasy)

204
00:05:39,110 --> 00:05:40,070
Are you nervous?

205
00:05:40,070 --> 00:05:40,790
A little.

206
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:41,720
Don't be.

207
00:05:41,963 --> 00:05:43,070
You'll have to introduce me.

208
00:05:43,270 --> 00:05:44,200
Of course.

209
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:46,600
Maybe we'll have games today.

210
00:05:47,320 --> 00:05:48,640
There will surely be.

211
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:49,600
What are you good at?

212
00:05:50,110 --> 00:05:50,950
How about running?

213
00:05:51,263 --> 00:05:52,160
You'll need to sprint.

214
00:05:52,160 --> 00:05:52,950
I can do that.

215
00:05:53,510 --> 00:05:54,550
When you were kids,

216
00:05:54,550 --> 00:05:56,440
did they time your 50-m sprint

217
00:05:56,440 --> 00:05:57,510
in seconds?

218
00:05:57,830 --> 00:05:58,625
What was your time?

219
00:05:58,636 --> 00:05:59,519
Do you still remember?

220
00:05:59,720 --> 00:06:00,720
Ours was 100.

221
00:06:00,950 --> 00:06:02,040
Both 50 and 100 for us.

222
00:06:02,950 --> 00:06:05,350
In primary school, I was slow.

223
00:06:05,880 --> 00:06:06,950
14 s, if I remember right.

224
00:06:07,320 --> 00:06:08,160
14 s?

225
00:06:08,802 --> 00:06:10,082
I don't remember my time exactly.

226
00:06:10,093 --> 00:06:10,790
Not sure if it was

227
00:06:10,790 --> 00:06:11,386
the 50-m sprint

228
00:06:11,397 --> 00:06:12,320
or some other distance.

229
00:06:12,320 --> 00:06:13,510
I ran it in just over 8 s.

230
00:06:13,510 --> 00:06:14,756
It must've been the 50-m sprint.

231
00:06:15,510 --> 00:06:16,760
That's pretty fast.

232
00:06:20,670 --> 00:06:22,390
Are there any games you're scared of,

233
00:06:22,390 --> 00:06:23,790
if we have to play later?

234
00:06:24,070 --> 00:06:24,950
I'm scared of water.

235
00:06:25,440 --> 00:06:26,640
Anything else? Balance?

236
00:06:26,950 --> 00:06:27,720
A little bit.

237
00:06:28,510 --> 00:06:29,270
I'm not great

238
00:06:29,270 --> 00:06:30,200
at pulling things.

239
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:31,720
I'm not that strong.

240
00:06:32,920 --> 00:06:34,950
If you work out,
your arm strength must be solid.

241
00:06:34,950 --> 00:06:35,880
Not bad.

242
00:06:38,230 --> 00:06:39,880
Can you do that?

243
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:40,640
Pull-up.

244
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:43,270
With assistance.

245
00:06:43,270 --> 00:06:44,183
I can if it's assisted.

246
00:06:44,194 --> 00:06:45,423
If you ask me to just grab it,

247
00:06:45,450 --> 00:06:46,830
I can't do it on my own.

248
00:06:46,830 --> 00:06:47,830
You can totally do it.

249
00:06:47,830 --> 00:06:48,790
Yeah, I can.

250
00:06:50,270 --> 00:06:51,600
The sky is so blue today.

251
00:06:52,160 --> 00:06:52,950
Seriously?

252
00:06:52,950 --> 00:06:53,790
These days,

253
00:06:53,790 --> 00:06:55,480
the sky was all gray.

254
00:06:57,093 --> 00:06:58,670
The sun seemed to have dipped a little.

255
00:06:58,670 --> 00:06:59,550
Do you feel that?

256
00:07:00,340 --> 00:07:02,260
(Feeling it)

257
00:07:02,350 --> 00:07:03,920
Just a little.

258
00:07:05,640 --> 00:07:06,510
Not so dazzling.

259
00:07:08,480 --> 00:07:10,270
Do you like daytime or nighttime better?

260
00:07:10,760 --> 00:07:11,640
Nighttime.

261
00:07:13,193 --> 00:07:14,670
Because the sun's not strong at night?

262
00:07:18,310 --> 00:07:20,670
Do you like going on island vacations?

263
00:07:20,670 --> 00:07:21,996
Do you enjoy traveling in general?

264
00:07:22,283 --> 00:07:23,230
Yeah, I love traveling.

265
00:07:23,790 --> 00:07:24,640
Me too.

266
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:26,760
I've always wanted to come to Sanya.

267
00:07:27,550 --> 00:07:28,230
Perfect.

268
00:07:28,666 --> 00:07:29,320
You're here now.

269
00:07:29,320 --> 00:07:30,320
I think it's nice.

270
00:07:30,663 --> 00:07:32,390
So, we've got to take a walk
along the sea.

271
00:07:32,390 --> 00:07:33,510
We're leaving here

272
00:07:33,510 --> 00:07:34,790
in just a bit.

273
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:35,510
True.

274
00:07:35,510 --> 00:07:36,110
Are you done?

275
00:07:37,510 --> 00:07:38,110
Shall we go?

276
00:07:38,390 --> 00:07:38,830
Let's go.

277
00:07:43,640 --> 00:07:44,830
Seriously.

278
00:07:44,830 --> 00:07:45,640
So cozy.

279
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:47,640
Yeah, I think so.

280
00:07:48,510 --> 00:07:50,790
This is their famous white sand beach.

281
00:07:50,801 --> 00:07:52,110
It looks different in the daytime.

282
00:07:52,110 --> 00:07:53,480
Pretty, right?

283
00:07:53,480 --> 00:07:54,040
Yeah.

284
00:07:57,920 --> 00:08:00,040
Do you feel like touching the water?

285
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:00,760
I do.

286
00:08:00,760 --> 00:08:01,640
Wanna give it a try?

287
00:08:01,640 --> 00:08:02,920
Let me see if it's cold.

288
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:03,670
Let me see.

289
00:08:03,670 --> 00:08:04,640
Just a light touch.

290
00:08:04,640 --> 00:08:05,320
Wait.

291
00:08:05,320 --> 00:08:06,510
It won't get me wet, right?

292
00:08:06,843 --> 00:08:07,510
I don't think so.

293
00:08:07,510 --> 00:08:08,640
Wait for it.

294
00:08:12,390 --> 00:08:13,320
I'm touching it.

295
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:16,390
Not cold.

296
00:08:20,720 --> 00:08:21,720
Wow, it's not cold.

297
00:08:21,720 --> 00:08:22,550
Right?

298
00:08:22,550 --> 00:08:24,110
It's warm; the sun's blazing.

299
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:30,670
That sound is so calming.

300
00:08:30,670 --> 00:08:32,670
Yeah, it's beautiful.

301
00:08:35,710 --> 00:08:36,640
That's awesome.

302
00:08:36,640 --> 00:08:37,440
Look at them.

303
00:08:38,350 --> 00:08:39,640
I wanna lie down here too.

304
00:08:39,640 --> 00:08:40,840
Me too.

305
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:42,230
Very chill, right?

306
00:08:49,883 --> 00:08:50,640
Wanna check it out?

307
00:08:50,640 --> 00:08:51,710
What's this?

308
00:08:51,710 --> 00:08:52,550
Let's watch it.

309
00:08:52,550 --> 00:08:53,910
I wanna see.

310
00:08:55,110 --> 00:08:56,520
Anything cute for you?

311
00:08:57,268 --> 00:08:58,102
This one's adorable.

312
00:08:58,113 --> 00:08:58,910
It's wearing a hat.

313
00:08:58,910 --> 00:09:00,710
I think you like white.

314
00:09:00,710 --> 00:09:01,710
Like your...

315
00:09:01,710 --> 00:09:04,030
Like our family dog.

316
00:09:04,030 --> 00:09:05,400
With hats, they look alike.

317
00:09:05,400 --> 00:09:05,910
Ultraman.

318
00:09:05,910 --> 00:09:07,230
Did you like Ultraman as a kid?

319
00:09:07,400 --> 00:09:08,110
Not really.

320
00:09:08,110 --> 00:09:08,790
Not really?

321
00:09:08,790 --> 00:09:10,000
What did you like?

322
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:11,840
I loved Crayon Shin-chan.

323
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:12,910
Me too.

324
00:09:12,910 --> 00:09:14,230
Let me tell you something.

325
00:09:14,382 --> 00:09:16,099
I'm gonna do
a Crayon Shin-chan impression.

326
00:09:16,110 --> 00:09:16,756
Can you do that?

327
00:09:16,767 --> 00:09:17,683
Do you want to hear it?

328
00:09:17,694 --> 00:09:18,384
Sure.

329
00:09:20,520 --> 00:09:21,320
Don't laugh.

330
00:09:25,500 --> 00:09:28,060
(Focused and waiting)

331
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:30,590
Hang on a sec.

332
00:09:30,590 --> 00:09:31,610
Let me get into character.

333
00:09:41,670 --> 00:09:43,280
Misae, you're back!

334
00:09:44,470 --> 00:09:46,000
Misae, you're back!

335
00:09:50,760 --> 00:09:52,150
Let's go.

336
00:09:52,150 --> 00:09:53,215
That was hilarious.

337
00:09:53,226 --> 00:09:53,960
I've started doing

338
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:54,960
Shin-chan's voice now.

339
00:09:54,960 --> 00:09:55,790
Sounds about right.

340
00:09:56,320 --> 00:09:57,470
Doesn't it?

341
00:09:57,470 --> 00:09:58,080
Yeah.

342
00:09:58,080 --> 00:09:59,200
Don't do that again.

343
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:00,350
Don't do that again?

344
00:10:08,230 --> 00:10:09,840
Did it work?

345
00:10:09,840 --> 00:10:10,710
What?

346
00:10:10,710 --> 00:10:11,520
I haven't tried it.

347
00:10:11,520 --> 00:10:12,470
Not yet?

348
00:10:12,710 --> 00:10:13,880
It got too late last night.

349
00:10:13,893 --> 00:10:15,150
(Day 2 night, a foot bath basin)

350
00:10:15,150 --> 00:10:16,440
You fell into water today.

351
00:10:16,440 --> 00:10:18,150
You'll need this.

352
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:19,150
Thanks.

353
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:21,590
Thank you.

354
00:10:22,470 --> 00:10:23,400
It's nothing.

355
00:10:24,230 --> 00:10:25,030
More oil.

356
00:10:27,590 --> 00:10:29,760
This is our guys' territory.

357
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,790
I'll handle the fire and cooking.

358
00:10:32,790 --> 00:10:34,030
Sure.

359
00:10:36,960 --> 00:10:38,230
This pot's got a name.

360
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:40,910
What name?

361
00:10:41,110 --> 00:10:43,080
Look, it says here:

362
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:45,200
75869752.

363
00:10:45,200 --> 00:10:45,960
Nice name.

364
00:10:46,266 --> 00:10:47,150
(Big applause)
Later,

365
00:10:47,150 --> 00:10:48,350
I'll have name like that.

366
00:10:49,400 --> 00:10:50,590
What if you forget me?

367
00:10:50,590 --> 00:10:52,000
Think about what it's called.

368
00:10:52,230 --> 00:10:53,790
It's called...

369
00:10:54,280 --> 00:10:55,640
75869752.

370
00:10:58,320 --> 00:10:59,110
Sorry.

371
00:10:59,790 --> 00:11:00,470
It's fine.

372
00:11:00,710 --> 00:11:02,000
I seemed to have touched you.

373
00:11:03,650 --> 00:11:04,590
Do it a few more times.

374
00:11:05,840 --> 00:11:08,150
I don't know how to respond to that.

375
00:11:08,150 --> 00:11:09,640
It's fine, no need to respond.

376
00:11:09,640 --> 00:11:10,840
That's awkward.

377
00:11:11,140 --> 00:11:13,020
(So sweet)

378
00:11:13,030 --> 00:11:14,550
75869752.

379
00:11:14,550 --> 00:11:15,440
I've memorized it now.

380
00:11:15,670 --> 00:11:16,470
Good.

381
00:11:16,470 --> 00:11:17,400
Will you remember me?

382
00:11:17,710 --> 00:11:18,840
Yeah.

383
00:11:18,840 --> 00:11:20,640
Your name is...

384
00:11:26,110 --> 00:11:27,670
Feels like that pancake.

385
00:11:29,280 --> 00:11:30,280
Not bad.

386
00:11:41,030 --> 00:11:43,400
Why did they all head out?

387
00:11:43,400 --> 00:11:44,590
Let's step outside.

388
00:11:50,230 --> 00:11:51,000
Is that high enough?

389
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:52,320
A bit higher.

390
00:11:52,440 --> 00:11:53,590
Alright, I'll push harder.

391
00:11:55,150 --> 00:11:55,790
Okay, perfect.

392
00:11:55,790 --> 00:11:56,590
Thanks.

393
00:11:57,670 --> 00:11:58,910
What game will it be today?

394
00:11:58,910 --> 00:12:00,200
Will we team up today?

395
00:12:00,790 --> 00:12:01,590
No idea.

396
00:12:01,590 --> 00:12:03,280
We didn't team up the past two days.

397
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:05,400
I've been thinking about it.

398
00:12:05,400 --> 00:12:06,106
There's definitely

399
00:12:06,117 --> 00:12:07,440
gonna be newcomers.

400
00:12:08,030 --> 00:12:09,200
I think so.

401
00:12:11,540 --> 00:12:12,613
What are you talking about?

402
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:14,350
(Request to join)
Someone new.

403
00:12:14,790 --> 00:12:15,790
Our talk?

404
00:12:15,790 --> 00:12:17,880
It's about little secrets.

405
00:12:18,670 --> 00:12:19,880
You went all in, right?

406
00:12:20,110 --> 00:12:21,740
(Center of attention)
You went all in?

407
00:12:21,760 --> 00:12:21,983
Yeah.

408
00:12:21,994 --> 00:12:23,543
(Firmly)
You've made a choice so early.

409
00:12:23,590 --> 00:12:24,470
Absolutely.

410
00:12:24,840 --> 00:12:25,066
Yeah.

411
00:12:25,550 --> 00:12:26,350
Listen.

412
00:12:26,350 --> 00:12:28,760
Before yesterday's date,

413
00:12:28,760 --> 00:12:29,880
he didn't really show much.

414
00:12:30,230 --> 00:12:31,150
You'll notice

415
00:12:31,150 --> 00:12:32,590
that before yesterday's date,

416
00:12:32,590 --> 00:12:34,350
he barely talked to her.

417
00:12:34,590 --> 00:12:35,230
Yeah.

418
00:12:35,230 --> 00:12:36,790
When the date happened,

419
00:12:36,790 --> 00:12:37,643
I felt it was a chance

420
00:12:37,654 --> 00:12:38,743
for him to express himself.

421
00:12:38,754 --> 00:12:39,880
Once he says it out loud,

422
00:12:39,880 --> 00:12:41,960
he'll start getting closer.

423
00:12:42,230 --> 00:12:42,590
Well.

424
00:12:42,590 --> 00:12:45,030
I'm not exactly afraid

425
00:12:45,030 --> 00:12:46,670
of a crowd.

426
00:12:46,670 --> 00:12:47,376
Most of the time,

427
00:12:47,387 --> 00:12:49,670
I prefer

428
00:12:49,670 --> 00:12:50,880
one-on-one chats.

429
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:55,280
How did that conversation go?

430
00:12:55,470 --> 00:12:56,200
Pretty good.

431
00:12:56,200 --> 00:12:56,960
We talked a lot.

432
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:58,200
Got a lot out of it?

433
00:12:58,200 --> 00:12:59,230
Yeah.

434
00:12:59,230 --> 00:13:00,180
(So sweet)

435
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:02,000
A question for you.

436
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:03,350
Are you feeling unsure now?

437
00:13:03,350 --> 00:13:03,790
Today?

438
00:13:03,790 --> 00:13:04,400
Yeah.

439
00:13:04,470 --> 00:13:04,910
Not at all.

440
00:13:04,910 --> 00:13:05,670
Still not?

441
00:13:05,670 --> 00:13:06,960
Let's wait until after today.

442
00:13:08,760 --> 00:13:10,000
I'll always have your back.

443
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:11,000
Just go for it.

444
00:13:15,790 --> 00:13:16,760
Is this real?

445
00:13:17,163 --> 00:13:19,029
(Whether the branch is real)
I think it's fake.

446
00:13:19,150 --> 00:13:20,400
Do you think it just fell there,

447
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:22,230
or is it a prop?

448
00:13:23,230 --> 00:13:23,880
A prop.

449
00:13:23,880 --> 00:13:25,200
It was made

450
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:25,790
just for you.

451
00:13:26,230 --> 00:13:26,959
For me?

452
00:13:26,970 --> 00:13:27,200
Yeah.

453
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:28,960
Only you would play

454
00:13:28,960 --> 00:13:29,760
with this thing.

455
00:13:30,470 --> 00:13:31,550
Do you think I'm childish?

456
00:13:31,550 --> 00:13:32,640
I think you're cute.

457
00:13:32,640 --> 00:13:33,640
You're cute.

458
00:13:34,030 --> 00:13:35,500
(Cheered up)
Right?

459
00:13:35,520 --> 00:13:36,340
Such a fancy life.

460
00:13:36,351 --> 00:13:37,200
I'm not used to this.

461
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:38,640
(Fancy, cute)
Too fancy.

462
00:13:38,640 --> 00:13:39,590
You should be fancy too.

463
00:13:39,590 --> 00:13:40,790
Do you have any fancy clothes?

464
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:42,700
(I do)
Yeah.

465
00:13:42,700 --> 00:13:43,710
I have them.

466
00:13:43,710 --> 00:13:44,230
(I think...)

467
00:13:44,230 --> 00:13:45,000
On your fancy day,

468
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:45,710
I'll be ordinary.

469
00:13:47,280 --> 00:13:48,400
I'll "shoot" them all.

470
00:13:55,520 --> 00:13:56,520
Indifferent.

471
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:00,230
This spot is perfect

472
00:14:00,230 --> 00:14:01,350
for...

473
00:14:01,350 --> 00:14:02,470
Paintball.

474
00:14:02,536 --> 00:14:04,000
(Paintball?)
Doesn't it splash color?

475
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:05,840
Paintball guns are high-end.

476
00:14:05,840 --> 00:14:08,030
They have laser sights.

477
00:14:08,030 --> 00:14:09,880
You'll have a laser point on you.

478
00:14:09,880 --> 00:14:11,470
Once you're hit, you're out.

479
00:14:11,840 --> 00:14:13,470
I need to hide, right?

480
00:14:13,470 --> 00:14:14,470
I need to hide.

481
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:15,960
Listen.

482
00:14:15,960 --> 00:14:17,110
If we team up for this game,

483
00:14:17,110 --> 00:14:17,760
we won't lose.

484
00:14:17,771 --> 00:14:19,400
(Mark my words)
I'll be in front of you.

485
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:20,393
No one's getting past me.

486
00:14:20,404 --> 00:14:21,751
(Winning by size advantage)
True.

487
00:14:21,762 --> 00:14:22,880
I'll stay behind you.

488
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:23,790
Exactly.

489
00:14:24,200 --> 00:14:25,640
We'd be perfect at playing

490
00:14:25,640 --> 00:14:27,110
eagle and chicks.

491
00:14:27,110 --> 00:14:27,910
What?

492
00:14:29,080 --> 00:14:29,550
Yeah, true.

493
00:14:29,550 --> 00:14:30,960
We'd still be tough to beat.

494
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:34,670
Then you'll be the eagle.

495
00:14:34,670 --> 00:14:35,660
(Rivals now?)

496
00:14:35,960 --> 00:14:36,590
Me? The eagle?

497
00:14:36,590 --> 00:14:37,320
Yeah.

498
00:14:37,590 --> 00:14:40,910
(Is this the eagle?)
The eagle's supposed to catch.

499
00:14:40,910 --> 00:14:42,000
Then what will you be?

500
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:43,880
I'll be the lead chick.

501
00:14:43,880 --> 00:14:46,020
(The one looking out for you)

502
00:14:46,030 --> 00:14:47,200
Mother hen.

503
00:14:49,150 --> 00:14:50,320
Are you afraid of elimination?

504
00:14:52,400 --> 00:14:52,880
Of course.

505
00:14:52,880 --> 00:14:55,150
But I also think it's okay.

506
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:59,440
Ideally, it should be mutual affection.

507
00:15:00,030 --> 00:15:01,840
If not, we shouldn't settle.

508
00:15:06,150 --> 00:15:07,400
Why did you get the most votes?

509
00:15:09,400 --> 00:15:11,150
Well, maybe

510
00:15:11,150 --> 00:15:12,200
I talk a lot.

511
00:15:12,760 --> 00:15:14,550
They see me as cheerful,

512
00:15:14,550 --> 00:15:17,000
so they give me some weights.

513
00:15:17,230 --> 00:15:18,440
It's a casual choice.

514
00:15:19,350 --> 00:15:21,590
After they picked a guy they liked,

515
00:15:22,273 --> 00:15:22,960
they'd wonder

516
00:15:22,971 --> 00:15:24,196
where the last weight could go.

517
00:15:24,207 --> 00:15:25,289
They couldn't go all in,

518
00:15:25,300 --> 00:15:26,320
so they gave it to me.

519
00:15:26,840 --> 00:15:27,960
That's how I see it.

520
00:15:29,230 --> 00:15:30,030
Not necessarily.

521
00:15:30,400 --> 00:15:30,910
Really?

522
00:15:30,910 --> 00:15:31,590
Not necessarily.

523
00:15:31,960 --> 00:15:33,440
I don't care about the weights

524
00:15:33,590 --> 00:15:35,150
of the other girls.

525
00:15:35,520 --> 00:15:37,590
I'm pretty curious about yours.

526
00:15:37,790 --> 00:15:38,960
How did you guys guess?

527
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:41,230
Not telling you that.

528
00:15:41,550 --> 00:15:43,590
Let's wait for the final reveal.

529
00:15:43,590 --> 00:15:44,230
Alright.

530
00:15:48,820 --> 00:15:51,340
(Homely boyfriend)

531
00:15:56,440 --> 00:15:57,985
Why are you always here?

532
00:15:57,996 --> 00:15:58,550
Is that right?

533
00:15:58,550 --> 00:15:59,760
A fixed position for you.

534
00:15:59,760 --> 00:16:00,150
Seriously?

535
00:16:00,150 --> 00:16:00,583
Yeah.

536
00:16:00,594 --> 00:16:01,280
I don't think so.

537
00:16:01,280 --> 00:16:02,213
You were here yesterday.

538
00:16:02,224 --> 00:16:02,640
The same.

539
00:16:02,640 --> 00:16:04,790
The sink was also clogged.

540
00:16:04,860 --> 00:16:06,590
(The previous night)

541
00:16:06,590 --> 00:16:07,760
Do you need help?

542
00:16:08,440 --> 00:16:09,760
No, we can handle it ourselves.

543
00:16:09,760 --> 00:16:10,590
It's clogged.

544
00:16:10,780 --> 00:16:13,100
(Same spot, same people)

545
00:16:13,310 --> 00:16:14,000
Same thing today.

546
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:14,910
Exactly.

547
00:16:15,150 --> 00:16:16,550
Felt like déjà vu.

548
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:18,840
Déjà vu.

549
00:16:19,960 --> 00:16:21,200
You're honestly so good

550
00:16:21,200 --> 00:16:23,080
at housework, right?

551
00:16:23,080 --> 00:16:24,670
Just look at the way he does it.

552
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:25,280
Yeah.

553
00:16:27,030 --> 00:16:29,710
I like things neat and tidy.

554
00:16:30,640 --> 00:16:31,840
Bonus points.

555
00:16:31,840 --> 00:16:32,740
(Points, points)

556
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:36,550
See?

557
00:16:36,550 --> 00:16:40,180
(Clean and tidy)

558
00:16:40,790 --> 00:16:42,350
You're so considerate.

559
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:45,590
We haven't cleaned this up.

560
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:50,150
I meant to tell you something yesterday.

561
00:16:50,150 --> 00:16:51,710
But I went to do an interview.

562
00:16:52,200 --> 00:16:52,760
What is it?

563
00:16:52,760 --> 00:16:53,230
Go ahead.

564
00:16:53,230 --> 00:16:54,790
Based on my first impression

565
00:16:54,790 --> 00:16:56,030
of you,

566
00:16:56,400 --> 00:16:57,760
plus your Beijing accent,

567
00:16:58,030 --> 00:17:00,400
I figured you might be hard
to get along with.

568
00:17:01,550 --> 00:17:03,000
You can call me Michael.

569
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:05,830
My Chinese name is Zhang Zizheng.

570
00:17:05,830 --> 00:17:07,000
I made two dishes.

571
00:17:07,830 --> 00:17:09,590
That was my thought back then.

572
00:17:10,110 --> 00:17:10,760
Seeing some

573
00:17:10,760 --> 00:17:13,000
of the things you did yesterday

574
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:14,350
made me realize

575
00:17:14,350 --> 00:17:15,950
first impressions aren't that accurate.

576
00:17:15,950 --> 00:17:18,040
We need more time together

577
00:17:18,040 --> 00:17:19,113
and go through a few things

578
00:17:19,124 --> 00:17:21,560
to get to know each other.

579
00:17:21,710 --> 00:17:22,230
Yeah.

580
00:17:22,230 --> 00:17:23,662
Like what?

581
00:17:23,673 --> 00:17:24,230
I don't know.

582
00:17:24,241 --> 00:17:24,710
For example,

583
00:17:24,710 --> 00:17:27,000
you took care of Huang.

584
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:29,160
He had a leg cramp yesterday.

585
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:29,920
A cramp?

586
00:17:29,920 --> 00:17:30,560
Here, take this.

587
00:17:30,560 --> 00:17:32,040
You helped him stretch it out.

588
00:17:32,040 --> 00:17:33,560
When Yijia

589
00:17:33,560 --> 00:17:34,190
fell in,

590
00:17:34,760 --> 00:17:37,070
you rushed to save her.

591
00:17:38,103 --> 00:17:38,880
That's when I felt

592
00:17:38,880 --> 00:17:39,680
that your actions

593
00:17:39,680 --> 00:17:41,000
show you're thoughtful

594
00:17:41,190 --> 00:17:43,040
deep down,

595
00:17:43,040 --> 00:17:44,400
not just pretending to be nice.

596
